##

to launch AdeskBar :
adeskbar <config_file>

Config files : ~/.config/adeskbar/
Install dir : /usr/share/adeskbar/
Log file : ~/.config/adeskbar/output.log

---

Install
-------

sudo ./install.sh
or
su -c "./install.sh"

unInstall
---------

sudo ./uninstall.sh
or
su -c "./uninstall.sh"


---

Create .deb package for Debian / Ubuntu

sudo ./make_deb.sh
or
su -c "./make_deb.sh"

---

Dependencies
------------

python , python-gtk2 , python-cairo  , python-gmenu ( usually already installed )

optional : python-dbus

plugin : 

    - python-wnck :         tasklist/showdesktop
    - python-alsaaudio :    volume  ( python-pyalsaaudio on Arch / Slitaz )
    - python-vte :          terminal
    - python-xlib :         systray

for Debian / Ubuntu :

    sudo apt-get install python-wnck python-alsaaudio python-vte python-xlib python-dbus


